  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment (environmental gap variant)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). The CPB device is deployed in operating-room environments where ambient temperature can range 18–26°C, electromagnetic interference from surgical equipment is present, and elevation-dependent ambient pressure variations of ±15 mmHg are routine. All validation experiments were conducted under controlled laboratory conditions at 22°C and standard atmospheric pressure; no environmental-sensitivity study characterizing the effect of these parameter ranges on model predictions has been performed.",
  "assuranceLevel": "Medium",
  "couName": "CPB use",
  "decision": "Accepted",
  "deviceClass": "Class II",
  "modelRiskLevel": 2,
  "bindsRequirement": "https://uofa.net/synth/req/morrison-cou1-hemolysis-rh",
  "bindsClaim": "https://uofa.net/synth/claim/morrison-cou1-worst-case-hemolysis",
