    "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/decision/morrison-cou1-accepted-2026",
    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/morrison-credibility-assessment-team",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All seven assessed credibility factors meet or exceed the required gradation levels for Model Risk Level 2. The six not-assessed factors are acceptable at MRL 2 per the ASME V&V 40 factor applicability matrix. The CFD model is accepted as credible for identifying worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for the Class II CPB device. Predicted RH < 1 at all five operating points supports the regulatory submission. The assessment team notes that all validation activities were conducted under controlled laboratory conditions (22°C, 101.3 kPa) and that the clinical deployment environment involves temperature variation (18–26°C), ambient pressure variation, and electromagnetic interference from surgical equipment; however, no formal environmental sensitivity study was deemed necessary at MRL 2 given the medium model influence classification.",
    "decidedAt": "2026-04-19T00:00:00Z"
